  "The potential energy of a substance at height": "",
  "The total kinetic energy of all particles in a substance due to their random motion": "",
  "Energy from the sun": "",
  "Thermal energy is the total kinetic energy associated with the random motion of all atoms and molecules in a substance; it depends on both temperature and the amount of substance.": "",
  "What does 'heat capacity' mean?": "",
  "The rate at which heat is transferred": "",
  "The maximum temperature a substance can reach": "",
  "The ability of a substance to store chemical energy": "",
  "The amount of heat required to raise the temperature of an object by 1 degree C": "",
  "Heat capacity (C) is the amount of heat needed to raise the temperature of an entire object (not per gram) by one degree Celsius.": "",
